        "title": "Remove the souls feature end to end",
        "body": "## What this removes\n\nSOULS turned out to be three layers, all gutted here (90 files, +301/−6754):\n\n- The flag-gated UI (`VITE_FEATURE_SOULS`, default off): nav/footer links, homepage category, `/souls` + `/souls/$slug` routes, publish soul-mode\n- A whole second-brand site: \"SoulHub\" served at `onlycrabs.ai` via hostname-based `getSiteMode()` — site.ts collapsed to ClawHub-only constants\n- The always-on backend: six Convex tables (`souls`, `soulVersions`, `soulVersionFingerprints`, `soulEmbeddings` incl. vector index, `soulComments`, `soulStars`), the public `/api/v1/souls` HTTP API, soul search, soul OG images, GitHub soul backups, and seeds\n\nSurviving skills-only code was de-branched and simplified along the way: tag resolution lost its souls generic (and its `as never` casts), the publish form is single-mode, the ban flow returns a plain `deletedSkillComments` count, and the now-inert nav gating machinery was deleted.\n\n## Deliberate decisions\n\n- `/souls` URLs and `/api/v1/souls` return plain 404s — no redirect, no 410 tombstone (owner decision)\n- Reserved slugs `souls` / `soulhub` / `onlycrabs` stay reserved (squatting protection)\n- `CHANGELOG.md` history untouched\n\n## ⚠️ Deploy prerequisite (prod)\n\nProd holds 21 soul rows and 4 uploaded SOUL.md blobs. **Before deploying this PR**, a Convex admin must, in the Production deployment (`wry-manatee-359`) dashboard:\n\n1. Delete 4 file-storage blobs: `kg200td050ae5dk0gh9w2xy5b583q5c5`, `kg21y0bpr4t7z4365x02gqcsbn7yzj4r`, `kg24cbkh3xzf8tas2kkmwpye5580djck`, `kg293zkzg2yy8cnj9q359yrp2h7yzag` (blobs first — the rows are their only in-product index)\n2. Delete the six `soul*` tables (expected rows: souls 4, soulVersions 4, soulVersionFingerprints 4, soulEmbeddings 4, soulComments 1, soulStars 4)\n3. Deploy **full** (not backend-only — avoids cached bundles calling deleted functions)\n\nContent is backed up locally (rows + all four SOUL.md files). Dev (`admired-dodo-615`) soul tables are empty. The `clawdbot/souls` backup repo doesn't exist. The next `clawhub` CLI npm release should version for the removed `ApiRoutes.souls` export.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `tsc --noEmit` (root + packages/schema + packages/clawhub): clean\n- `vitest run` full suite: 3001 passed, 1 pre-existing skip\n- `oxlint`, `oxfmt --check`, `knip` deadcode (files/deps/exports): clean\n- `vite build`: clean; `routeTree.gen.ts`, `convex/_generated/api.d.ts`, `packages/schema/dist` verified drift-free against regeneration\n- Rendered UI validated with Playwright at desktop + mobile against the dev deployment: home (3-column categories, no souls text), header/footer, search routing, `/souls` 404s cleanly, publish page renders; zero console errors\n- Review: two-phase until-clean — built-in code-review workflow (5 iterations, 8 findings fixed) then 3 independent cold-review passes, all clean on this exact tree\n\nNot verified: Playwright e2e suites (souls entries removed by grep-verified edits only); authenticated publish form verified in source, not rendered.",
